    public class GUISimulationPicker
extends javax.swing.JDialog
implements java.awt.event.KeyListener
    GUISimulationPicker is a dialog to collect the details required for approximate (simulation-based) model checking: initial state, max path length, simulation method + parameters, etc.

        public GUISimulationPicker(GUIPrism parent,
                           java.util.List<Expression> exprs,
                           ModulesFile modulesFile,
                           java.lang.String titleExtra)
                    throws PrismException
        Create a new GUIConstantsPicker dialog to define info for simulation-based property checking.
        Parameters:
        parent - Parent GUI window
        exprs - The properties to be checked (note: constants may not be defined)
        modulesFile - The model that will be simulated (for initial state info)
        titleExtra - Optional string to append to dialog (null if not needed)
        Throws:
        PrismException - if there is a problem getting initial state info from the model.
